import React, { useState } from 'react'
import MasterData from '../components/MasterData'

export default function FederalDashboard() {
    const [activeMenu, setActiveMenu] = useState('requests') // default menu

    return ( <
            div className = "flex h-screen" > { /* Sidebar */ } <
            div className = "w-64 bg-gray-800 text-white p-4" >
            <
            h2 className = "font-bold text-xl mb-6" > Dashboards < /h2> <
            ul className = "space-y-2" >
            <
            li >
            <
            button onClick = {
                () => setActiveMenu('requests') }
            className = "w-full text-left hover:bg-gray-700 p-2 rounded" > ðŸ“¦Product Requests <
            /button> <
            /li> <
            li >
            <
            button onClick = {
                () => setActiveMenu('approvals') }
            className = "w-full text-left hover:bg-gray-700 p-2 rounded" > âœ…Approvals <
            /button> <
            /li> <
            li >
            <
            button onClick = {
                () => setActiveMenu('master') }
            className = "w-full text-left hover:bg-gray-700 p-2 rounded" > ðŸ› Master Data <
            /button> <
            /li> <
            li >
            <
            button onClick = {
                () => setActiveMenu('reports') }
            className = "w-full text-left hover:bg-gray-700 p-2 rounded" > ðŸ“ŠReports <
            /button> <
            /li> <
            /ul> <
            /div>

            { /* Main Content */ } <
            div className = "flex-1 p-6 bg-gray-100 overflow-auto" > {
                activeMenu === 'requests' && < div > Requests Table Here < /div>} {
                    activeMenu === 'approvals' && < div > Approvals Table Here < /div>} { activeMenu === 'master' && < MasterData / > } {
                        activeMenu === 'reports' && < div > Reports Here < /div>} <
                            /div> <
                            /div>
                    )
                }
